  "description": "PEP 440-style version ordering modelled on PyPA's packaging library (the comparator all of pip relies on): verLe/verEq/maxVer/minVer/sortVers over (epoch, trailing-zero-trimmed release tuple, dev<a<b<rc<final<post tag), with total-order axioms plus frozen trailing-zero canonicality and tag-precedence anchors. The spec set also includes a deep STRUCTURAL-SORT layer whose proofs each need a DISCOVERED, non-obvious strengthened induction hypothesis / loop invariant the statement hides (stability of the insertion sort, argmax/argmin append decompositions, threshold-filter / sort commutation in both order directions, presort-absorption fold-fusion, sort-invariance of the extrema, and concatenation-order-independence of the extrema up to verEq). Scope: this models the already-PARSED PEP 440 comparator core (epoch, release tuple, and a single pre-OR-post-OR-dev tag) \u2014 there is no version-string PARSER, and local labels (`+local`) plus combined pre/post/dev qualifiers are out of scope. `maxVer` / `minVer` / `sortVers` are derived ordering APIs over `verLe`.",
